# Build Bible V2 — Chapter 12 (Enterprise Paddle Billing)

Spec: `docs/14_BUILD_BIBLE_V2_CHAPTER_12_PADDLE_BILLING.md`

## Rules

- Paddle is the sole active billing provider (`getActiveBillingProvider()` → `"paddle"`).
- Entitlements resolve only via `resolveOrganizationEntitlements` after verified sync.
- Never grant access from browser checkout success callbacks.
- Webhooks: verify signature, enforce idempotency, fail safely, never corrupt billing state.
- Emit commercial analytics only through `trackBillingLifecycleEvent` / `emitPaddleWebhookCommercialEvent` without org/customer IDs.
- Keep secrets server-only (`PADDLE_API_KEY`, `PADDLE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`).
- Do not reintroduce Stripe as an active checkout/portal path.
- Do not change auth, RBAC, RLS, SEO, accessibility, or analytics architecture outside billing hooks.

## This chapter

- Do not commit, push, or deploy from Chapter 12 work.
